8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 978, L.D. 1494, “Resolve, Directing the
10 Office of Procurement Services to Study Adapting the Procurement Process to the State
11 Climate Action Plan”
12 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the 4th to 6th lines (page 1, lines 4 to 6 in L.D.) by
13 striking out the following: "and all quasi-independent agencies, boards, commissions,
14 authorities and institutions, as well as with the legislative branch and the judicial branch"
15 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the 8th line (page 1, line 8 in L.D.) by inserting after
16 the following: "plan."" the following: 'The office shall exclude from the study procurements
17 conducted by the Public Utilities Commission for energy or transmission infrastructure
18 pursuant to Title 35-A.'
19 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
20 section number to read consecutively.
21 SUMMARY
2222 This amendment amends the resolve by removing all quasi-independent agencies,
2233 boards, commissions, authorities and institutions, as well as the legislative and judicial
2244 branches, from the list of entities the Department of Administrative and Financial Services,
2255 Office of Procurement Services must coordinate with for the study. The amendment also
2266 amends the resolve by stating that the office must exclude from the study procurements
2277 conducted by the Public Utilities Commission for energy or transmission infrastructure
2288 pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 35-A.
2299 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3300 (See attached)
